Findings: Moderate cardiomegaly is stable. Note is made of aortic and coronary artery calcifications, notably in the LAD. Generalized chronic interstitial abnormalities remain unchanged. No focal pulmonary abnormality is identified to suggest pneumonia. There is no large pleural effusion or pneumothorax.
Impression: Unchanged chronic interstitial abnormalities with no acute cardiopulmonary process.
